memory_get_usage()  ===> used to calculate the RAM used by this PHP process.

When you run a PHP script (like your MVC app), PHP allocates memory in RAM to:
    - The PHP engine itself
    - All loaded classes (like HomeController, Autoload, etc.)
    - Variables, arrays, objects, functions
    - Built-in PHP structures (strings, numbers, etc.)

Using top or htop to see the Active Script Proccess in RAM Memory

Inside .htaccess file :
  - RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f → If the requested URL isn’t a real file
  - RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d → And isn’t a real directory
  - RewriteRule ^(.*)$ index.php → Send it to index.php for routing


  MVC URL Structure : Domain/ControllerName/ActionName

  trim($string, "x") in PHP, it only removes the specified characters from the beginning and the end of the string. It does not remove them from the middle.
  trim($url) removes the whitespaces from the beginning and the end of the string,


  ucfirst() ==> make first char as uppercase

  use : sudo a2dissite 000-default.conf ===> to prevent default Apache page on the root page

  array_shift() removes the first element of an array and returns it (array_shift(array &$array) Takes an array by reference 
  so it modifies the original array and Returns the removed first element) $numbers = [10, 20, 30]; becomes [20, 30]